│ THOUGHT: The issue is that LLVM's instcombine pass is incorrectly transforming a copysign operation into an fabs followed by fneg when the function has a nofpclass attribute that    │
│ excludes positive values. The problem occurs with signaling NaN (SNaN) values - the original copysign preserves the sign bit of the second argument, but the transformation always    │
│ makes the result negative, which changes the sign bit of SNaN values and thus produces different results. I need to find the instcombine optimization that performs this              │
│ transformation and add a check to prevent it when the transformation would change the behavior for NaN values.                                                                        │
│                                                                                                                                                                                       │
│ Let me first locate the relevant LLVM source files that handle copysign optimizations in instcombine.                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                                                                       │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                               │
│ find /llvm-autofix -name "*.cpp" | xargs grep -l "copysign.*fabs\|fabs.*copysign" 2>/dev/null || find /llvm-autofix -name "*InstCombine*" -type f -name "*.cpp"                       │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                   │
